<p>From our first auxiliary hospital built in 1955, The Good Samaritan Society has grown to over 54 sites and programs that serve more than 6,000 individuals. Inspired by the parable of the Good Samaritan, we provide complex/long term care, assisted/supportive living and other specialized health care services for the elderly and the physically and mentally challenged, regardless of race or religious belief.

The Society receives all clients with honour and respect and offers them the care and support they need. Housing options, care programs and services are provided in a wide range of environments, including:

Alzheimer/Dementia Care Programs
Assisted/Supportive Living
Community Short-Stay/Respite Programs
Complex/Long Term Care
Corporate and Administrative Services
Day Programs
Life Lease and Seniors Apartments
Programs for Persons with Disabilities – Group homes and supportive roommate program
Seniors’ Health Clinic
Sub Acute Care
Good Samaritan TeleCare® Emergency Response
Young Adult Programs for Persons with Physical Disabilities
The Good Samaritan Society is committed to providing a quality of care and support that will enable the elderly and the physically and mentally challenged to experience an optimum quality of life. Security, independence and a sense of belonging are enjoyed by clients in Good Samaritan facilities and programs. As a leading provider of housing and health care support, The Good Samaritan Society has played a key role in the development of new and innovative programs – programs that have become industry standards throughout Canada.</p>
